statement.p:
Write the equation with integer coefficients.

\dfrac{1}{4}x+z=\dfrac{3}{4}

\dfrac{2}{3}x-2y+\dfrac{1}{2}z=3

li.p:
We multiply both sides of the equation by \alert{4}.
        \alert{4} \cdot \left(\dfrac{1}{4}x+z\right) \amp = \left(\dfrac{3}{4}\right) \cdot \alert{4}
            x+4z \amp = 3

We multiply both sides of the equation by the LCD of the fractions, \alert{6}.
        \alert{6} \cdot \left(\dfrac{2}{3}x-2y+\dfrac{1}{2}z\right) \amp = (3) \cdot \alert{6}
            4x-12y+3z \amp = 18
